<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910221-0158</DOCNO><DOCID>910221-0158.</DOCID><HL>   United Industrial Contract</HL><DATE>02/21/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><CO>   UIC</CO><IN>AEROSPACE (ARO)AIRLINES (AIR)</IN><GV>TRANSPORTATION DEPARTMENT (TRN)DEFENSE DEPARTMENT (DEF)COMMERCE DEPARTMENT (COM)</GV><LP>   NEW YORK -- United Industrial Corp. said its AAI Corp.unit was awarded an initial $18.9 million to provideautomated weather observing and reporting systems at U.S.airports.   The 24-hour systems are to replace routine surface weatherobservations collected manually at about 950 weatherstations. The systems, updated each minute, will give pilotsweather information through computer-generated voice messagesas they approach 800 airports.</LP><TEXT>   Jointly sponsored by the U.S. departments of Commerce,Transportation and Defense, the contract is part of themodernization of the National Weather Service. The initialphase calls for units to be installed at about 40 airportsthis summer.   United Industrial is a defense contractor that makeselectronic test and training equipment.</TEXT></DOC>